Basics

Install miSCutils

R is an open-source statistical environment which can be easily modified to enhance its functionality via packages. miSCutils is a R package available via GitHub repository. R can be installed on any operating system from CRAN after which you can install miSCutils by using the following commands in your R session:

install.packages("devtools")

devtools::install_github("gtwa-bio/miSCutils")

Required knowledge

miSCutils is based on many other packages and in particular in those that have implemented the infrastructure needed for dealing with single-cell/single-nuclei RNA-seq and ATAC data. That is, packages like Seurat and DESeq2 .

Asking for help

As package developers, we try to explain clearly how to use our packages and in which order to use the functions. But R and Bioconductor have a steep learning curve so it is critical to learn where to ask for help. The blog post quoted above mentions some but we would like to highlight the Bioconductor support site as the main resource for getting help: remember to use the miSCutils tag and check the older posts. Other alternatives are available such as creating GitHub issues and tweeting. However, please note that if you want to receive help you should adhere to the posting guidelines. It is particularly critical that you provide a small reproducible example and your session information so package developers can track down the source of the error.

Citing miSCutils

We hope that miSCutils will be useful for your research. Please use the following information to cite the package. Maybe one day we’ll have a real DOI. Thanks!

## Citation info
citation("miSCutils")

Reproducibility

The miSCutils package (gtwa-bio, 2024) was made possible thanks to:

  • R (R Core Team, 2024)
  • BiocStyle (Oleś, 2024)
  • knitr (Xie, 2024)
  • RefManageR (McLean, 2017)
  • rmarkdown (Allaire, Xie, Dervieux, McPherson, Luraschi, Ushey, Atkins, Wickham, Cheng, Chang, and Iannone, 2024)

This package was developed using biocthis.
